PrismLauncher - Use for minecraft, allows you to create geometric shapes instead of placing thousands of blocks manually, also have it on second drive, so main drive doesn't lose multi gigs
Markdown# Fixing Minecraft on Arch Linux with Prism Launcher (Full Guide)

## 1. Install & Setup Prism Launcher
```bash
sudo pacman -Syu prismlauncher
prismlauncher  # Launch to verify
2. Install Java (for MC 1.17+)
Bashsudo pacman -S jre21-openjdk-headless  # Primary
# Optional for older MC versions:
sudo pacman -S jre8-openjdk-headless jre17-openjdk-headless
3. Prepare Secondary Drive (e.g., /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft)
Bashsudo mkdir -p /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/{instances,mods,resourcepacks,icons,java}
sudo chown $USER:$USER /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft
chmod -R 755 /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft
4. Configure Prism for Secondary Drive

Open Prism Launcher.
Settings (gear icon) → Launcher tab → Folders:
Instances Folder: /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances
Mods Folder: /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/mods
Resource Packs: /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/resourcepacks
Icons Folder: /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/icons

Java tab: Enable "Download Java automatically" or select system Java.
OK → Restart Prism.

5. Create Fabric/Quilt Instance (for WorldEdit)

Add Instance:
Loader: Fabric or Quilt.
MC Version: e.g., 1.21.1.
Name: e.g., "1.21.11".

OK → Instance creates in /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances/1.21.11.

6. Install WorldEdit Mod

Right-click instance → Edit → Mods tab.
Download Mods → Search WorldEdit (EngineHub).
Filter: Fabric/Quilt + your MC version.
Install → Close → Launch once to verify.

7. Add Old World from ZIP Backup
Bashcd /mnt/sdb5/
unzip "2025-12-27_12-20-22_CherrySean.zip"  # Extracts CherrySean/
mkdir -p /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances/1.21.11/minecraft/saves
cp -r CherrySean /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances/1.21.11/minecraft/saves/
ls /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances/1.21.11/minecraft/saves/CherrySean  # Verify: level.dat, region/
8. Launch & Verify

Prism → Select 1.21.11 → Launch.
Minecraft → Singleplayer → CherrySean appears → Play.
WorldEdit: //wand (get tool), //sel, //set stone (test).

Troubleshooting

No saves folder: Launch instance once (creates structure).
Version mismatch: Match MC version to world.
Crashes: Check latest.log; install Fabric API if missing.
NVIDIA: prime-run prismlauncher.
Move existing instances: rsync -avh old/path/ /mnt/sdb5/Minecraft/instances/.

Notes

All data on secondary drive – main SSD stays clean.
WorldEdit works in singleplayer (full perms).
Backup worlds: cp -r saves/YourWorld ~/backup/.
